node.text:
about the award-winning SCUBAPRO Seahawk 2 BCD. 

@scubadivingmag ScubaLab tested the Scubapro Seahawk 2 in its 2019 BCD review.

With a travel-friendly design that doesn’t compromise on stability, comfort, or amenities, it was their Testers Choice for travel BCDs.

ScubaLab tested BCDs, also called or buoyancy compensators—at Blue Grotto Dive Resort in Central Florida.

They conducted objective tests in the pool to measure each BC’s buoyant lift and inherent buoyancy and gauge its ability to cope with a runaway power inflator.

ScubaLab also conducted a series of test dives to evaluate each BC in ten categories, including comfort, stability, and ascent control.

#scubapro #awardwinning #bcd #buoyancycompensators #scuba #diving #divegear #dive #equipement #deepdownyouwantthebest

node.text:
"Sometimes a new piece of gear offers a feature or capability we didn’t realize we were missing that turns out to be a game-changer. That was the case with Scubapro’s Galileo HUD, a mask-mounted dive computer that makes it surprisingly easy to constantly monitor critical dive info while keeping your hands free." @scubadivingmag 

Read the entire review from Roger Roy and Robby Myers by visiting https://www.scubadiving.com/scubapro-galileo-hud-scubalab-innovation-award-winner

#scubapro #gaileohud #divecomputer #scubadiving #deepdownyouwantthebest
